rComments: Took her for Women Religion and Law. Well structured class, I learned a lot. I felt like the group discussion welcomed disagreement and I always felt comfortable expressing myself. Definitely a hard class to do well in, but fair. Also very accessible outside of class, even with COVID crisis

For this course, she is very good. But it would be better if her slides offer more specific contents. Regarding the exam, she offers many in-class practice questions and sets out clear expectations in her review practice exam sessions.

Lectures constitute of her mechanically reading off her notes. Hard to keep up with her, as she speaks so quickly and her slides are completely insufficient. Does not teach in an impartial manner, and imposes her bias on every topic ie. religious rights, domestic contracts etc.
TALKS WAY TOO FAST. Hard to tell whether she's rapping or lecturing. In all other aspects, she is an excellent professor.
She is a good professor. Always found her lectures interesting, but could also do the readings if I missed the class and still be able to know and understand the material.

TERRIBLE prof. While she missed class due to unavoidable family medical issues, she did not seek to mitigate the effects of her absences. podcasted lectures, but did not review them in class.  Mechanic lecturer and talks too fast and softly.Classtime felt disjointed and confusing. Prof did not entertain questions and treated with disdain
Great class and prof.  Progressive and smart.
Very clear Professor. Very articulate and really knows her stuff. Friendly, approachable and into social justice issues. I thought she was great!
SOOOO boring!! She is too "by the book". Lots of small assignments worth very little.
